not being in the office.

04:08.873 --> 04:10.375
How's Ashley?

04:10.400 --> 04:12.070
Is she okay?

04:12.072 --> 04:15.340
II don't know her. II mean,
I... I just met her last night.

04:15.342 --> 04:16.975
She gave me her number, I...

04:16.976 --> 04:18.310
Is she okay?

04:18.312 --> 04:20.012
Well, for the record, Mr. Graham,

04:20.014 --> 04:21.313
we're being recorded.

04:21.315 --> 04:23.382
And I want to just make sure it's clear

04:23.384 --> 04:25.350
you're here of your own volition, right?

04:25.352 --> 04:27.286
You understand that you're
free to leave at any time.

04:27.288 --> 04:29.655
No, I get that.
And I want to help. I just...

04:29.657 --> 04:32.591
I kind of need to know what's going on.

04:33.548 --> 04:34.960
Okay.

04:36.931 --> 04:41.199
So, last night was the first time ever

04:41.201 --> 04:43.613
you saw Ashley Richardson, right?

04:45.372 --> 04:47.239
She's dead, Mr. Graham.

04:49.981 --> 04:52.077
Her body was found
in the park this morning.

04:52.079 --> 04:53.735
My God.

04:54.778 --> 04:56.882
She'd been beaten, raped,

04:56.884 --> 04:59.700
bitten on the neck, strangled to death.

05:01.159 --> 05:03.822
My God.

05:03.824 --> 05:06.091
Man, I...

05:06.093 --> 05:08.750
That's horrible, that's...

05:10.731 --> 05:13.332
Now, we have security video
that shows you and Ashley

05:13.334 --> 05:15.968
outside the bar after everyone else left.

05:15.970 --> 05:17.936
Nobody else is on the tape.

05:18.343 --> 05:20.272
You two were the only ones out there.

05:24.445 --> 05:26.578
So you were drunk and high.

05:26.580 --> 05:27.813
Yes, sir.

05:27.815 --> 05:31.116
And you wanted to have
sex with this girl. Right?

05:31.118 --> 05:33.919
I mean, I wanted to see her again,

05:33.921 --> 05:35.487
if that's what you're asking.

05:35.489 --> 05:37.389
I'm starting to think
maybe I should leave.

05:37.391 --> 05:38.690
I'm starting to think

05:38.692 --> 05:40.859
that I need to come back
with an attorney.

05:40.861 --> 05:43.729
Well, you're ccertainly free to do that.

05:43.731 --> 05:45.964
Look, you've been nothing
but cooperative. If...

05:45.966 --> 05:47.565
It's just, you know,
it's just thesethese questions.

05:47.567 --> 05:48.965
II just think that you might want

05:48.967 --> 05:50.819
to take a second and think
about how that would look.

05:50.821 --> 05:53.271
I mean, if you have nothing to hide.

05:53.273 --> 05:54.606
I don't.

05:54.608 --> 05:56.441
Again, totally up to you.

05:56.965 --> 05:59.244
But I do think you want
to give some consideration

05:59.246 --> 06:02.414
as to the appearance
that that would create.

06:07.621 --> 06:10.255
I've been here for what,
like, five hours?

06:10.257 --> 06:12.991
I haven't been keeping track of time.

06:12.993 --> 06:15.442
But yeah, we've been here a while.

06:15.876 --> 06:18.667
And like I said, I think you've
been nothing but cooperative.

06:18.669 --> 06:20.532
Do you think we're close to being done?

06:20.534 --> 06:21.733
I do.

06:21.735 --> 06:24.169
You got to tell me the truth,
Derrick. You're in it, kid.

06:24.171 --> 06:26.738
All that booze and the drugs.

06:26.740 --> 06:29.007
I mean, your memory's pretty spotty.

06:29.009 --> 06:31.343
You ever blacked out before, Derrick?

06:31.833 --> 06:33.345
II don't know. I've...

06:33.347 --> 06:35.680
- II don't think so.
- Come on.

06:35.682 --> 06:38.183
Maybe once, in college. Maybe twice.

06:38.185 --> 06:40.018
So it's possible.

06:40.020 --> 06:41.553
You could've blacked out. I don't know.

06:41.555 --> 06:43.555
I feel like I remember
everything that happened.

06:43.557 --> 06:46.725
Okay, here's the thing, Derrick.

06:46.727 --> 06:49.027
Ashley lived for a couple of hours

06:49.029 --> 06:50.862
after she was found in the park.

06:50.864 --> 06:52.330
I spoke to her.

06:52.332 --> 06:55.700
And she identified you as her attacker.

06:58.193 --> 06:59.905
Ashley said I did it?

07:00.445 --> 07:02.707
Have no reason to lie, would she?

07:02.709 --> 07:04.342
No, but, I mean...

07:04.344 --> 07:06.011
She was intubated,
so she couldn't actually speak.

07:06.013 --> 07:07.312
But I asked her to write down

07:07.314 --> 07:09.381
the name of the guy who did this to her.

07:09.383 --> 07:10.882
You want to see what she wrote?

07:10.884 --> 07:13.552
Yeah, sure, of course.

07:18.292 --> 07:21.493
This is Ashley's handwriting.

07:22.896 --> 07:25.397
I mean, I don't know, Derrick.

07:25.399 --> 07:27.532
Maybe you hurt her without meaning to.

07:27.534 --> 07:29.901
I'm just saying
it could've been an accident.

07:31.672 --> 07:34.039
Here's the proof.

07:36.877 --> 07:38.810
It's okay.

07:38.812 --> 07:40.812
Then, one night, you can't sleep.

07:40.814 --> 07:43.081
You start digging through
professional journals

07:43.083 --> 07:44.983
you've been meaning to read, and...

07:44.985 --> 07:47.152
and there it is.

07:47.154 --> 07:49.087
Courts all over the country

07:49.089 --> 07:52.224
are starting to reject
bite mark evidence.

07:53.627 --> 07:55.227
The legal community,

07:55.229 --> 07:58.169
courts, lawyers, law enforcement,

07:58.832 --> 08:02.100
a lot of them no longer believe
there's anything to it.

08:02.102 --> 08:04.469
And that matters because...?

08:04.471 --> 08:05.971
Derrick Graham.

08:09.243 --> 08:11.143
When I went into
the trial science business,

08:11.145 --> 08:13.812
one of the first trials
I was involved with

08:15.053 --> 08:16.314
was a murder trial.

08:16.316 --> 08:19.417
A, young investment banker
was accused

08:19.419 --> 08:23.255
of raping and killing a young
woman one night in a park.

08:23.257 --> 08:25.323
Downtown Manhattan.

08:25.325 --> 08:27.157
The Wall Street Slayer.

08:27.628 --> 08:30.495
Well, obviously you did
your job; Guy's in prison.

08:30.497 --> 08:31.863
No.

08:32.871 --> 08:34.456
I lost.

08:35.169 --> 08:37.034
I was working for the defense.

08:37.037 --> 08:38.270
And I believed with all my heart

08:38.272 --> 08:39.804
that he was innocent; I still do.

08:39.806 --> 08:41.573
Where are we going with this?

08:41.575 --> 08:44.176
The D.A. had three key pieces
of evidence.

08:44.178 --> 08:46.545
First, DNA evidence.

08:46.547 --> 08:48.580
My client's DNA was found on the victim.

08:48.582 --> 08:50.882
And he admitted that was because
he was kissing her

08:50.884 --> 08:52.484
earlier in the evening.

08:52.486 --> 08:55.120
Wait a second. I remember this case.

08:55.122 --> 08:56.821
Didn't he confess?

08:56.823 --> 08:59.925
A coerced confession, yes.

08:59.927 --> 09:01.393
A false confession.

09:01.395 --> 09:03.195
And that's piece number two.

09:03.197 --> 09:04.930
The detectives lied to the suspect,

09:04.932 --> 09:06.898
something they're allowed to do
in New York state,

09:06.900 --> 09:09.734
and I think we did a pretty good
job of making that clear

09:09.736 --> 09:11.242
to the jury.

09:11.772 --> 09:14.439
But then there was bite mark evidence.

09:14.441 --> 09:16.841
Which is now starting
to be considered bogus.

09:16.843 --> 09:18.043
Wait.

09:18.045 --> 09:19.778
Okay, you got me on two out of three.

09:19.780 --> 09:23.848
But an Ivyeducated investment
banker confessed to a murder

09:23.850 --> 09:25.350
he did not commit?

09:25.352 --> 09:26.716
They lied to him.

09:27.087 --> 09:29.988
They told him
the victim had identified him

09:29.990 --> 09:31.890
just before she succumbed
in the hospital.

09:31.892 --> 09:34.359
My client was in shock; He was upset

09:34.361 --> 09:36.194
and confused.

09:36.196 --> 09:39.864
I'm telling you, this man is innocent.

09:54.848 --> 09:56.348
Dr. Bull.

09:56.350 --> 09:57.749
Been a while.

09:59.207 --> 10:01.419
You think so?

10:04.424 --> 10:07.826
This is gonna sound hollow,
but I have wanted to visit.

10:08.258 --> 10:09.494
I know.

10:10.301 --> 10:12.230
I got your messages from way back when.

10:12.232 --> 10:16.167
I just... couldn't.

10:16.169 --> 10:19.304
You, my friends, my parents,

10:19.306 --> 10:21.062
even my sister.

10:22.856 --> 10:24.733
Haven't seen a one of them.

10:25.984 --> 10:28.403
I just kept saying no,
and they stopped asking.

10:29.487 --> 10:31.349
Well, thank you for saying yes
this one time,

10:31.351 --> 10:33.451
and let me tell you why I'm here.

10:33.453 --> 10:35.053
Bite mark evidence is no longer

10:35.055 --> 10:37.222
anyone's gold standard for anything.

10:37.224 --> 10:41.026
More and more courts
are refusing to recognize it.

10:45.766 --> 10:48.767
I'd like to file a motion
to vacate the guilty verdict.

10:48.769 --> 10:50.969
See if we can't get you a new trial.

10:50.971 --> 10:53.104
I'd like to fix this
for you, Derrick. I'd...

10:53.106 --> 10:56.808
I'd like to get you your life back.

10:56.810 --> 10:58.877
Can I have your permission?

10:58.879 --> 11:02.747
Sure. What do I care?

11:04.451 --> 11:06.274
Here's the thing.

11:08.155 --> 11:12.023
All of this, you...

11:12.025 --> 11:14.282
everything that happened
after that night...

11:15.395 --> 11:17.535
it's all just a dream, man.

11:18.518 --> 11:20.218
And I'm really just asleep.

11:22.069 --> 11:24.736
Either that or I'm dead,
and this is death.

11:27.941 --> 11:29.506
